    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-05-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-07-14T20:15:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Tax Code Termination Act - Mandates the termination of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 after December 31, 2009, except for self-employment taxes, Federal Insurance Contributions Act taxes, and Railroad Retirement taxes. </p> <p>Declares that any new Federal tax system should be a simple and fair system that: (1) applies a low rate to all Americans; (2) provides tax relief for working Americans; (3) protects the rights of taxpayers and reduces tax collection abuses; (4) eliminates the bias against savings and investment; (5) promotes economic growth and job creation; and (6) does not penalize marriage or families. </p> <p>Requires that the new Federal tax system be approved by Congress in its final form by July 4, 2009.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
